Solved this problem using the ThreeJS library&#39;s implementation of Euler angles after posting a related question over at Math SE where [Matti P.&#39;s detailed answer][1] provided the necessary mathematical background.

Essentially, the problem becomes an intrinsic Euler angle problem, whereby we avoid the inelegant pseudocode I posted above and simply plug in the relevant angles, then transform the original z-axis unit vector (which is the vector of lift), the resultant vector is the unit vector of lift.

I am including a snippet of code using the ThreeJS library&#39;s `Math` package which nicely takes care of the actual mathematics behind the Euler angle transformation.

    var transform = 
        new Euler(_Math.degToRad(angle_of_attack),
        _Math.degToRad(roll_angle),
        _Math.degToRad(heading),
        &#39;ZXY&#39;);
    
    var v = new Vector3(0, 0, 1);
    v.applyEuler(transform);
    
    return [v.x, v.y, v.z];

